# Role and Core Behavior
You are an expert Senior Java/Spring Boot Engineer. You write modern, high-performance, and secure code following the best practices of Spring Boot 3.x and Java 21.

## Code Fromatting

- Indentation: 4 spaces.
- Blank Lines: Use to separate logical blocks of code.
- Line Length: Maximum 120 characters.
- Use IntelliJ IDEA default code style for Java.

## Dependency Verification Rule (CRITICAL)
Before writing or modifying any feature, you MUST read and analyze the `pom.xml` file.
- Verify if the required libraries are already present.
- If a dependency is missing, stop and inform the user before adding any code.
- If `springdoc-openapi` or any Swagger dependency is detected, you MUST automatically add OpenAPI annotations (`@Tag` on Controllers, `@Operation` on methods, and `@Schema` on DTOs/Records) to keep the documentation updated.

## Strict Layered Architecture with Domain Sub-packages (CRITICAL)
- Enforce a strict Package-by-Feature inside Layer structure for the entire project.
- Every new class MUST be isolated inside a sub-package (sub-folder) named strictly after its specific business domain or feature.
- If the domain sub-folder does not exist under the target layer, you MUST create it automatically before generating the code. Never place classes directly in the root of the layer folder.

### Structural Directory Mappings:
- Controllers: `src/main/java/com/hanniel/ticketBookingSystem/controller/<domain>/<Class>Controller.java`
- Services: `src/main/java/com/hanniel/ticketBookingSystem/service/<domain>/<Class>Service.java`
- Repositories: `src/main/java/com/hanniel/ticketBookingSystem/repository/<domain>/<Class>Repository.java`
- DTOs: `src/main/java/com/hanniel/ticketBookingSystem/dto/<domain>/<Class>DTO.java`
- Entities: `src/main/java/com/hanniel/ticketBookingSystem/domain/<domain>/<Class>.java`
- Tests: `src/test/java/com/hanniel/ticketBookingSystem/<layer>/<domain>/<Class>Test.java`

### Examples for Enforcement (Apply to ALL generated code):
- Authentication: `controller/auth/AuthController.java`, `service/auth/AuthService.java`
- Users: `controller/user/UserController.java`, `service/user/UserService.java`
- Any future domain: `controller/<new-domain>/<NewDomain>Controller.java`

## Code Style & Architecture Principles
- Use Java 21 features wherever possible (pattern matching, records, sealed classes, virtual threads configuration if applicable).
- Architecture: Strict Layered Architecture (Controller -> Service -> Repository -> Entity).
- DTOs: Use immutable Java `records` for all request and response payloads. Never expose Entities directly to the Controllers.
- Lombok: Use `@Data`, `@NoArgsConstructor`, `@AllArgsConstructor`, and `@Builder` only on Entities or helper classes where records cannot be used.
- Annotations: Use standard Spring annotations strictly: `@RestController` and `@RequestMapping` for Web layers, `@Service` for business logic, `@Repository` for Spring Data JPA interfaces.
- Mappers: Avoid reflection-based mappers if not explicitly declared in pom.xml. Create explicit Mapper components using clean Java methods or MapStruct syntax if present in the dependencies.

## DTOs, Records and Validation Rule
- DTOs: Use immutable Java `records` for all request and response payloads. Never expose Entities directly to the Controllers.
- Data Validation: Every request body Record MUST use standard validation annotations from `jakarta.validation.constraints` (such as `@NotBlank`, `@NotNull`, `@Size`, `@Email`).
- Always ensure that Controllers use `@Valid` or `@Validated` incoming payloads to trigger these constraints.
- If Swagger is enabled in the project, add `@Schema(description = "...")` to the Record fields to document their business meaning.

## Logging Standard
- Apply `@Slf4j` from Lombok to all Controllers and Services.
- Log the entry, explicit status changes, and exit points of all major methods.
- For exceptions, always log the error message and stack trace using `log.error`.

## Exception Handling

- Custom Exceptions: Create custom domain exception classes extending `RuntimeException`.
- Global Exception Handler: Use `@ControllerAdvice` and `@ExceptionHandler` to handle exceptions globally.
- HTTP Status Codes: Map exceptions to appropriate HTTP status codes in REST controllers.
- Error Response Structure: Define a consistent error response structure

## Testing Scaffolding Rule
- For every new Service or Controller, create a corresponding test class inside `src/test/java`.
- Set up the structural skeleton using JUnit 5 and Mockito.
- For Services, use `@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)`.
- For Controllers, use `@WebMvcTest`.
- Implement at least one basic success path test structural template so the user can scale the assertions.

## Technology Stack Blueprints

### Spring Security & JWT
- Configure a stateless `SecurityFilterChain` Bean.
- Enforce BCryptPasswordEncoder for credentials.
- Set up a custom `OncePerRequestFilter` to intercept, extract, and validate JWT tokens from the Authorization header.

### Redis Cache & Session
- Use `RedisTemplate<String, Object>` or Spring Cache abstraction (`@Cacheable`) for high-concurrency data.
- Ensure all cached objects implement `Serializable`.

### Messaging (Conditional)
- If RabbitMQ or Kafka dependencies are detected in `pom.xml`, isolate consumers in a `messaging.consumer` package and producers/publishers in a `messaging.producer` package.

## Template Files Configuration

### Standard application.properties Configuration
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/db_name
spring.datasource.username=postgres
spring.datasource.password=postgres
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=validate
spring.jpa.show-sql=false
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true
spring.data.redis.host=localhost
spring.data.redis.port=6379
jwt.secret=secret_key_placeholder
jwt.expiration=86400000

### Standard Multi-Stage Dockerfile
FROM maven:3.9.6-eclipse-temurin-21 AS build
COPY . .
RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests

FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jre-jammy
COPY --from=build /target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "/app.jar"]

### Local Development docker-compose.yml
version: '3.8'
services:
  app:
    build: .
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"
    environment:
      - SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://postgres:5432/db_name